body:
So I don't think this is right. We 'link' with gtest-all.cc to pick those
up. Last time I saw this bug was because there was no std::ostream&
operator<<(std::ostream&, string_ref) defined; it looks like this one's
failing because there's nothing defined for grpc_arg_type?

On Wed, Sep 2, 2015 at 2:59 PM David G. Quintas notifications@github.com
wrote:

> In particular, we use -I to include third_party/googletest/include and
> link with -lgtest, but we don't point to the libraries generated by
> third_party/googletest/ with -L. Therefore the system googletest libs are
> picked up and that has started creating conflicts. See below:
> 
> c++ -L./libs/opt/openssl -g  -fPIC -Llibs/opt -pthread    ./objs/opt/test/cpp/client/channel_arguments_test.o ./libs/opt/libgrpc++.a ./libs/opt/libgrpc.a ./libs/opt/libgpr.a  -lprotobuf -lpthread   -lrt -lm -lz -lpthread -lprofiler -ldl -Ithird_party/googletest/include -Ithird_party/googletest third_party/googletest/src/gtest-all.cc -lgflags -o ./bins/opt/channel_arguments_test
> ./objs/opt/test/cpp/client/channel_arguments_test.o: In function `testing::AssertionResult testing::internal::CmpHelperEQ<int, int>(char const*, char const*, int const&, int const&)':
> /usr/include/gtest/gtest.h:1337: undefined reference to`testing::internal::EqFailure(char const_, char const_, testing::internal::String const&, testing::internal::String const&, bool)'
> ./objs/opt/test/cpp/client/channel_arguments_test.o: In function `testing::AssertionResult testing::internal::CmpHelperEQ<unsigned long, unsigned long>(char const*, char const*, unsigned long const&, unsigned long const&)':
> /usr/include/gtest/gtest.h:1337: undefined reference to`testing::internal::EqFailure(char const_, char const_, testing::internal::String const&, testing::internal::String const&, bool)'
> ./objs/opt/test/cpp/client/channel_arguments_test.o: In function `testing::AssertionResult testing::internal::CmpHelperEQ<grpc_arg_type, grpc_arg_type>(char const*, char const*, grpc_arg_type const&, grpc_arg_type const&)':
> /usr/include/gtest/gtest.h:1337: undefined reference to`testing::internal::EqFailure(char const_, char const_, testing::internal::String const&, testing::internal::String const&, bool)'
> collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status
> 
> â€”
> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub
> https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/3210.
True. Interesting it's started failing now. This is at current HEAD on master branch.
Heh turns out ccache's cache was corrupted... a ccache -C seems to have solved the issue.
